<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2507: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Heath</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-16T14:00:00-05:00">September
                                    16, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>108. President <persName corresp="#p_VSJ1">Vincent</persName> today
                            issued a proclamation<note n="26" xml:id="d729fn26">Printed in <hi rend="italic">Le Moniteur</hi>, September 16, 1932, copy of
                                which was forwarded in despatch No. 497, September 16, 1932, from
                                the Chargé in Haiti.</note> very strongly defending the treaty and
                            pointing out the disadvantages to Haiti of its nonratification. Code
                            proclamation is being sent by air mail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>